{
  "stem": "14463.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What means [NON-ENGLISH] is it comes from the word, to hear, to listen.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The grandfather used to ask me, what actually I learned in the cheder during the week, pasha of the week.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was every Saturday morning.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then grandmother, Malka, used to come in after, I was a good boy, with the milk, and also with cake, like cheesecake, and poppy cake.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I love it till today, of course.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So and grandfather took a tremendous interest in his grandchildren.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I don't-- maybe I imagine, and maybe not, but he was extremely fond of me, extremely, and so was my grandmother, Malka.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now next question.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "What do you want to ask me?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "What do you remember of the festivals and the religious life that you had?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Festival life.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Before I tell you about the festivals in my family, let me just give you a little description of the city.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Chrzanow was a small city.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You could call it a big shtetl, you know?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was as small city.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was only 30,000 inhabitants.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Out of the 30,000 inhabitants, there was about 4,000 or 5,000 Polish people, and the rest were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So as I used to say, in Chrzanow, you don't need a calendar because you know when it's Friday night, when it's a Shabbos, when it's Yom Tovim.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the Yom Tovim were very-- first of all, every Friday night, it was a tremendous thing.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The whole family used to go together to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "All [NON-ENGLISH], beautifully dressed in the [NON-ENGLISH], that's a certain coats, with the gartels, with the shtreimel.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And the children were all beautifully dressed and going to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I came back from the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I always remember my father used to walk in, and with always a song.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
